title: Aquatics: Marina's Lastelic, El Toro's Parenteau, Troy's Herrera commit
text:
Â· posted by DAN ALBANO 
The aquatics commitments continue to roll. 
Marina distance ace Joseph Lastelic has committed to UC Santa Barbara, Irvine Novaquatics club coach Jeri Marshburn announced via Twitter. The senior placed 10th in the 500-yard freestyle at the Division 1 finals last season. 
El Toro water polo player Maddy Parenteau has committed to San Diego State, Chargers girls coach Justin Johnson reports. The senior racked up 69 goals, 44 assists and 63 steals last season to help the Chargers claim their first CIF title. 
Troy diver Cristian Herrera has committed to Notre Dame, he confirmed. He placed seventh at the CIF-SS Division 2 finals last season and third as a sophomore. 
Please send aquatics news to Dan Albano at dalbano@ocregister.com More from Blog: OC Varsity
